.TH "srp_parse_in" 9 "srp_parse_in" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
srp_parse_in \- parse an IP address and port number combination
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" srp_parse_in
.BI "(struct net *net "  ","
.BI "struct sockaddr_storage *sa "  ","
.BI "const char *addr_port_str "  ","
.BI "bool *has_port "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "net" 12
[in]  Network namespace.
.IP "sa" 12
[out] Address family, IP address and port number.
.IP "addr_port_str" 12
[in]  IP address and port number.
.IP "has_port" 12
[out] Whether or not \fIaddr_port_str\fP includes a port number.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Parse the following address formats:
- IPv4: <ip_address>:<port>, e.g. 1.2.3.4:5.
- IPv6: \[<ipv6_address>\]:<port>, e.g. [1::2:34]:5.
